cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO 

This paper deals with tasks that require joint understanding of visual information and natural language, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) since the paper focuses on object detection and image segmentation. The second most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) since the paper also deals with natural language processing. The paper also proposes a new module network approach, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with synthetic datasets and control over dataset bias, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
